Tbh this base makeup technique is quite popular back then on instagram. But the ‘contour’ shades are tend to be lot more darker than the natural one like the MUA did on this video.

And tbh using this kind of technique (applying slightly darker base then gradually lighter to highlight the centre of the face) makes your face have more dimension/less wide-looking. When you apply a light color all over your face and contour it later on certain parts, the face still looks big & wide on camera.

I’m saying this bcs Ive been using this technique ever since I discovered it years ago. ️
